
  General Mathematical Procedures from Astronomical Users' Library 
    (November, 1993)

    FITEXY      :   Linear Least-squares approximation in one-dimension 
                    (y = a + b*x), when both x and y data have errors 
    GAMMLN      :   Return the natural log of the gamma function
                    (equivalent to IDL 2.4.0 intrinsic function LNGAMMA)
    GAUSSIAN    :   Compute the 1-D Gaussian function and optionally the 
                    derivative at an array of points
    KSONE       :   Return the Kolmogorov-Smirnov statistic and associated 
                    probability for an array of data values and a 
                    user-supplied cumulative distribution function (CDF) of 
                    a single variable
    KSTWO       :   Return the Kolmogorov-Smirnov statistic and associated 
                    probability that two arrays of data values are drawn from 
                    the same distribution
    LINTERP     :   Linearly interpolate tabulated data from one data grid to 
                    another
    MINF_BRACKET :  Bracket a local minimum of a 1-D function with 3 points
    MINF_CONJ_GRAD: Find the local minimum of a scalar function of several 
                    variables using the Conjugate Gradient method 
                    (Fletcher-Reeves-Polak-Ribiere algorithm)
    MINF_PARABOLIC: Find a local minimum of a 1-D function up to specified 
                    tolerance
    MINF_PARABOL_D: Find a local minimum of a 1-D function up to specified 
                    tolerance, using the first derivative
    POIDEV      :   Return an integer random deviate drawn from a Poisson 
                    distribution with a specified mean
    POLINT      :   Interpolate a set of N points by fitting a polynomial of 
                    degree N-1
    POLY_SMOOTH :   Reduce noise in 1-D data (e.g. time-series, spectrum)
                    but retain dynamic range of variations in the data by
                    applying a least squares smoothing polynomial filter
    PROB_KS     :   Returns the significance level of an observed value 
                    of the Kolmogorov-Smirnov statistic 
    QSIMP       :   Integrate a function to specified accuracy using the 
                    extended trapezoidal rule
    QTRAP       :   Integrate a function to specified accuracy using the 
                    extended trapezoidal rule
    QUADTERP    :   Quadratically interpolate (3 point Lagrangian) a function 
                    Y = f(X) at specified grid points
    SIGMA       :   Calculate the standard deviation value of an array, or 
                    calculate the standard deviation over one dimension 
                    of an array as a function of all the other dimensions
    SIXLIN      :   Compute linear regression coefficients by six different 
                    methods (when errors in X and Y are not calculable)
    TABINV      :   To find the effective index of a function value in
                    an ordered vector
    TRAPZD      :   Compute the nth stage of refinement of an extended 
                    trapezoidal rule
    TSUM        :   Trapezoidal summation of the area under a curve
                    (formerly know as INTEG)
    ZBRENT      :   Find the zero of a 1-D function up to specified tolerance

